HEADWORD: Lepidoganoid
<hw>Lep`i*do*ga"noid</hw> <pr>(l⟦ecr⟧p`⟦icr⟧*d⟦osl⟧*g⟦amac⟧"noid
<it>or</it> -g⟦acr⟧n"oid)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>lepi`s</grk> <grk>-i`dos</grk>, a scale + E.
<ets>ganoid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of a division
(<ord>Lepidoganoidei</ord>) of ganoid fishes, including those that have
scales forming a coat of mail. Also used adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

